    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="535"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d535">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/3258</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Irkutsk</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_HEL1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Harris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d535fn1">Sent via the Legation in China.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Omsk</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">undated</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received November 22, 1918, 11.26
                            a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>197. It is possible that Czech and Siberian troops at Ekaterinburg and
                    Chelyabinsk fronts will refuse to recognize <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                        >Kolchak</persName> as dictator of all-Russian government. Soldiers
                    apparently feel that <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1">Kolchak</persName> is
                    supported by reactionary elements who wish the restoration of the monarchy.
                    General impression here is that <persName corresp="#p_KAAV1"
                    >Kolchak</persName>’s step is premature and that he will not last long.</p>
                <p>French Ambassador [Commissioner] <persName corresp="#p_RELG1">Regnault</persName>
                    and Japanese Consul G[eneral] <persName>Sato</persName> of Harbin at present in
                    Omsk.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_HEL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Harris</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
